name: "I DIG CARROTS" Print
description:
We definitely dig carrots -- doesn't everyone? Our most recent print celebrates this most tasty yet humble vegetable in all its orangeness. Sure to be popular with those who enjoy gardening, or just eating!

This print is bright and graphic; it looks attractive framed or on its own. 

The image is printed in 3 colors on extra-heavy, 100% cotton paper. This lovely, soft-white paper has a noticeable texture.

Print measures 9 x 12 inches.


Each print is meticulously and slowly printed on a vintage cylinder letterpress. No two are ever exactly alike. Color shades may vary slightly from what you see on your screen.

We carefully pack and ship each print in a protective sleeve and cardboard mailer.

(Frame/matte not included).

description:
This print depicts the historic flight of French aviator Louis Bleriot. This is an especially graceful image that will look wonderful anywhere you display it.

The small type in lower corner of print reads:

Views of Mount Fuji:
The back of a wave on the open sea off Kanagawa. French aviator Louis Bleriot circles above in his Monoplane X1.

The image is printed in 3 colors on soft-white, 100% cotton paper that is lightly textured and extra-heavyweight. 

Each print is meticulously and slowly printed on a vintage cylinder letterpress. No two are ever exactly alike.

name: FORD TRI-MOTOR AIRPLANE Print
description:
This print depicts the historic and stylish Ford Tri-Motor airplane. 

The image is printed in 3 colors on soft-white, extra heavy, 100% cotton paper. 

The print size is: 8-1/2 x 11 inches.

Small type on lower corner of print reads:

Over River Rouge 1938–
The Ford Tri-Motor was a rugged, all-purpose aircraft with distinctive corrugated metal skin. Though production stopped in 1933, Tri-Motors continued active flying service well into the 1960s.

The illustration is completely original and each print is meticulously and slowly printed on a vintage cylinder letterpress.


We carefully pack and ship each print in a protective sleeve and cardboard mailer.

Frame and matte not included.

name: CONSTELLATION AIRPLANE Print
description:
The quintessential passenger plane of 1950's air travel, the stylishly shaped Constellation was based on the profile of a dolphin. The plane's design was commissioned by Howard Hughes for his airline, TWA. 

The image is printed in 3 colors on soft-white, heavyweight, 100% cotton paper. 

The print size is: 8-1/2 x 11 inches.

Small type on lower corner of print reads:
Approach into LaGuardia 1956–
Storm clouds billow over the water off Great Neck.
Gleaming in the afternoon sun, an L-1049 Constellation descends into New York.


Each print is meticulously and slowly printed on a vintage cylinder letterpress. No two are ever exactly alike.

We carefully pack and ship each print in a protective sleeve and cardboard mailer.

(Frame & matte not included.)

name: AIR MAIL PLANE Print
description:
This print in our historic airplane series depicts the Dayton-Wright Liberty, a vintage 1920's - '30s model well-known for its essential use in delivering the U.S. mail.

The image is printed in 3 colors on soft-white, extra heavy, 100% cotton paper. 

The print size is: 8-1/2 x 11 inches.

Each print is meticulously and slowly printed on a vintage cylinder letterpress. No two are ever exactly alike.


Small type on lower corner of print reads:

Air Mail Special –
The Dayton-Wright Liberty, with its tractor-like body and DeHavilland DH-4 engine was the workhorse of early U.S. Air Mail service. With a top speed of 120 m.p.h. and a range of 370 miles, it still got the mail through in all kinds of weather.




We carefully pack and ship each print in a protective sleeve and cardboard mailer.

(Frame and matte not included.)
